  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [ ] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (0dc266d 2022-08-05T00:05:53.884289904Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge build\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nAttempting to auto install packages that are not autodetected is breaking our CI build (introduced in https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/commit/54191b6aada33a8a7c3593d135caa8179f167855). Since it is a monorepo, we use github refs with commit hashes in the `package.json` to manage the solidity dependencies. We install all of the dependencies first and then when running build, it says that it detects missing dependencies and then fails. I believe that the failure may be due to `git` not being installed on the machine in CI, but the dependencies were installed via `yarn` so I feel like it shouldn't try to install them.\r\n\r\nIs there any way that we could make this a configurable feature?",
